HUMAN remains have been discovered in the waters off the coast of Arbroath.
 Police swooped on Arbroath Harbour on Monday morning following reports that suspected human remains had been recovered seven miles from land. 
Tests have revealed the remains are human and further tests will be carried out to assist officers with their enquiries.
Experts hope to determine how long the remains have been in the water.
  
